channel.title: Anti-Leech
channel.description: I tried editing images in my cache through Tom's Cache Suite and after I was done, I saved and changed my client background then I compiled. I ran the client and noticed the client background didn't change. Then I logged in and no images were changed. How can I fix this?

item.title: Anti-Leech
item.dc:creator: @Ashton51 Ashton51
item.description:
@Ashton51 wrote:

[quote=“ytuio9, post:21, topic:386520”]sonsofgod2, realize that nobody wants you on this forum. Every topic you go on ends up turning into flame because of how stupid you are. Maybe if you actually took the time to learn Java you’d realize how much of a dumb fuck you are. The client does not compile the image - there is no need to turn it into machine language, it’s loaded during runtime, not compile time.
OP: This is more of a client help thing. Anyway they solved your problem.[/quote]
